channel.title: Error: Unable to startup listener on 43594- port already in use?
channel.description:
Jesus fucking christ, there is nowhere to find the solution for this sticky problem. Everything thats said is: "Port is already in use" NO FUCKING SHIT, SHERLOCK! So yeah, most of you who are reading this, are probably to say either what I said above or "CLOSE UTORRENT". Dont fucking post that shit, it drives me insane seeing how fucking dumb people can be. (Me dumb? No, im just new to this shit. Think things over before you post, and try to be USEFUL. I dont mind suggestions on what to do, just dont be STUPID).
Thanks.

item.title: Error: Unable to startup listener on 43594- port already in use?
item.dc:creator: @Tutorial Tutorial
item.description:
@Tutorial wrote:

You come about getting help in a terrible way, but as the same post above it clearly states your problem - your port is currently in use. I have no clue how you can go about finding which application is using the port, but all I can tell you is compare the current programs you have to default ports that the programs are set to run on. (Programs that require internet connection are usually the only programs that use ports because ports basically just handle the connection between incoming and outgoing packets.

Hope this helps…
